## 🔑 Memory Stages

```
ENCODING → CONSOLIDATION → STORAGE → RETRIEVAL
```

| Stage | Process | Duration | Neural Correlate |
|-------|---------|---------|----------------|
| **Encoding** | Acquisition of new information; depth of processing matters (elaborative > shallow) | Milliseconds–seconds | Hippocampus + PFC; attention-dependent |
| **Consolidation (synaptic)** | Stabilization of synaptic changes; protein synthesis-dependent; sensitive to disruption (concussion, anesthesia, ECT) | Minutes–hours | Early LTP → late LTP; CaMKII → CREB pathway |
| **Consolidation (systems)** | Hippocampus-dependent reactivation during sleep → gradual transfer to neocortex for long-term storage | Days–years | Hippocampal sharp-wave ripples (SWS) + cortical slow oscillations + thalamic spindles |
| **Storage** | Distributed representation in neocortex (semantic) or maintained hippocampal trace (episodic per MTT) | Permanent (ideally) | Synaptic weight changes; structural changes (spine density) |
| **Retrieval** | Reactivation of stored pattern; reconstruction (not playback) | Milliseconds | Hippocampus (cue-dependent); PFC (strategic retrieval) |

