## 🔑 Working Memory (Baddeley's Model)

Working memory is the active maintenance and manipulation of information over seconds (distinct from long-term memory). **Capacity: ~7 ± 2 items (Miller's law).**

| Component | Neural Substrate | Function |
|-----------|----------------|----------|
| **Central executive** | Dorsolateral PFC (bilateral) | Attentional control; coordinates subsystems; task switching; inhibition |
| **Phonological loop** | Left DLPFC + Broca's area + left premotor/parietal | Verbal/phonological rehearsal; inner speech; verbal WM; impaired in Broca's aphasia |
| **Visuospatial sketchpad** | Right PFC + posterior parietal (area 7) + right occipital | Visual and spatial information maintenance; impaired in right parietal lesions |
| **Episodic buffer** | Hippocampus + PFC | Integrates phonological + visuospatial + long-term memory into coherent episodes |

### Neural Correlates
- **Delay-period firing**: PFC neurons maintain sustained activity during delay period of delayed-match-to-sample tasks — proposed neural basis of WM
- **N-back paradigm**: classic fMRI task activating bilateral DLPFC (especially left for verbal, right for spatial)
- WM capacity predicts fluid intelligence, reading comprehension, and academic performance

